Have only tested this app by taking screenshots of static screens (not video or screen with moving images) so far, and it worked great! The provision of an on-screen capture button (faster than having to press down on two physical buttons & less wear and tear too!), plus the ability to disable animation & preview, makes it one of, if not the best, screenshot apps for quick successive captures, with no worries that a screenshot might inadvertently contain the animation/preview of the immediately preceding one. In fact, tested on a constantly refreshing stock index page (numbers change but nothing moves across the screen like in a video) and the "different" screenshots were all clear & sharp. The screenshots are saved to the stock screenshot folder by default which is what I wanted, but I understand you can choose another folder if you want. 5 stars!!!!!
